<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="203" data-end="586"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>"Before the Great Falling. Before corruption spread like a poison. Before the traitors and hopeless legions marched.</em></span><br data-start="321" data-end="324" /><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>There was an era of prosperity and might &mdash; when master artisans tempered blades worthy of emperors, when warriors grew heavy on silver and crimson victories, when women spun silken webs of intrigue, and when lords commanded with the authority of Heaven itself.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="588" data-end="726"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>Battles thundered across the land in the name of the Throne, summoning the boldest hearts to seize honor &mdash; or vanish into nameless dust.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="728" data-end="935"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>Every smith, every craftsman, every laborer poured their spirit into creation. The most gifted among them rose near the rank of sages, devoting their entire existence to the perfection of their sacred art.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="937" data-end="1078"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>In that radiant age, armors of peerless strength were born, forged with secrets that only the Grandmasters of the forge could summon forth.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="1080" data-end="1467"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>But now&hellip; all is swallowed by time.</em></span><br data-start="1114" data-end="1117" /><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>What lingers are but a few forgotten scrolls, guarded by generations scarred with sorrow, now crumbling in silence upon dust-laden shelves and within the hollowed ruins of forsaken citadels.</em></span><br data-start="1307" data-end="1310" /><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>Only fragments remain &mdash; scattered like stars across a broken world, waiting for one with courage to unearth them, claim them, and restore their brilliance.</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="1469" data-end="1601"><span style="color: #18a085;"><em>The Celestial Forge of perfection awaits you &mdash; step forward, and let your hands rekindle the eternal flame that shapes destiny."</em></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="460" data-end="592">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p data-start="132" data-end="299">This series of mods aims to introduce historically inspired armors into the game.<br data-start="213" data-end="216" />This one is dedicated to the medieval China, specificaly introduces armor of Song, and Ming dynasty.<br /><br /></p>
<p data-start="103" data-end="229">Armors added by this mod are somewhat improved versions of the vanilla items, which serve as the base for crafting these modded armors.<br />Chineese military was known for their archery skills, the armors are made in this image.</p>
<p data-start="231" data-end="489">&nbsp;</p>
<p data-start="231" data-end="489">You will, as always need a specific schematic, which can be found in newly generated ruins or may appear at the Treasure Trader (Useful traders compatible) once he restocks after you install this mod.<br data-start="408" data-end="411" />Due to the rarity of these schematics, their price won&rsquo;t exactly be a bargain.</p>
<p data-start="132" data-end="299">&nbsp;</p>
<p data-start="147" data-end="415">Anyway, as always if some errors pop up somewhere &mdash; let me know if you find some.<br data-start="226" data-end="229" />I&rsquo;m aware that the recipes are VERY expensive, and that&rsquo;s intentional &mdash; these armors represent very late-game technology. On the bright side, once crafted, the armor is easy to maintain.</p>
<p data-start="417" data-end="564">All feedback is welcome too, and the availability of this armor in survival mode can be rebalanced in the future if there&rsquo;s enough pushback.</p>
<h4 data-start="417" data-end="564"><strong>Compatibilities:</strong><br />Combat Overhaul<br />Useful Traders</h4>
<p data-start="417" data-end="564"><br /><br /></p>
