<h2 style="text-align: center;" data-start="566" data-end="581">Thanks to</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;" data-start="566" data-end="581"><span style="background-color: #34495e; color: #ecf0f1;">PrincessCrystal</span> for the commision<br /><span style="background-color: #e67e23;">DeanBro</span>&nbsp;for the uk translation<br /><span style="background-color: #27ae60;">JonR&nbsp;for</span> help with the native Combat Overhaul compatibility<br /><span style="background-color: #8e44ad; color: #ecf0f1;">Arcadria</span> for help with patching the traders to buy back the schematics</h2>
<p data-start="566" data-end="581">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;" data-start="566" data-end="581">Chronicle of The Great Jianyu<br /><br /></h3>
<h6 data-start="179" data-end="404"><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="179" data-end="190">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="190" data-end="193" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Master Liang Shen&hellip; every time I see these armors, <br />I feel they carry something more than iron. The Song lamella flows like water, <br />while the Ming plates stand firm like mountains. How can armor hold such spirit?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="406" data-end="421">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="421" data-end="424" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(smiles, his voice gentle yet steady, like the rhythm of the forge)</span></em><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><br />Spirit does not dwell in the iron, Jianyu. It is carried there by the hands that shape it. <br />Each plate, each knot of cord, each polish of the surface is more than labor&mdash;it is devotion. <br />But remember this: what you see here is not mine alone.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="737" data-end="748">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="748" data-end="751" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Not yours alone? But Master&hellip; your work is beyond compare!</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="812" data-end="827">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="827" data-end="830" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(laughs softly, shaking his head)</span></em><br data-start="863" data-end="866" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">A river flows because many streams feed it. My hands would falter if not for the guidance of other masters. <br />Eldred, for instance&mdash;his eyes are sharper than any blade. He sees flaws where others see perfection. <br />His criticism is not cruelty, but a gift. And the guilds themselves, by standing together, sharpen us all. <br />Without them, one smith is just a hammer in the dark. With them, we become the bell that rings clear across kingdoms.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1303" data-end="1314">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1314" data-end="1317" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">So even a master bows to other masters?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1360" data-end="1375">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1375" data-end="1378" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">To bow is not shame&mdash;it is strength. The guilds hold us to standards higher than our own pride. <br />Alone, we might grow careless, but among brothers of the craft, we are reminded that excellence <br />is born from honesty, even when it stings. That is why what you see here is polished not only by fire, but by fellowship.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1693" data-end="1704">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1704" data-end="1707" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">I see&hellip; then when I work, I do not carry only my hammer, but also the wisdom of the guild, and of masters like Eldred.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1828" data-end="1843">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1843" data-end="1846" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Exactly, Jianyu. Every stroke you make carries voices&mdash;those who taught you, <br />those who corrected you, those who stood beside you.<br /></span></em><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="2074" data-end="2085">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="2085" data-end="2088" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(his eyes shining with understanding)</span></em><br data-start="2125" data-end="2128" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Then I will work harder, Master. Not just for myself, but for all who stand with us.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="2216" data-end="2231">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="2231" data-end="2234" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(nods, his expression warm and proud)</span></em><br data-start="2271" data-end="2274" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Good. Remember&mdash;true honor is not in claiming credit, but in building something greater than yourself. <br />The guilds remind us of that. And if you hold to this spirit, one day your work will not only <br />protect bodies, but also preserve the unity that keeps us strong.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="163" data-end="174">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="174" data-end="177" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">But still, I am surprised. You speak so openly of the help of others, <br />as if your own work were not already legendary. Why would a man of your mastery reveal such&hellip; weakness?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="377" data-end="392">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="392" data-end="395" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(smiles gently, eyes glimmering like sparks in the forge)</span></em><br data-start="452" data-end="455" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Weakness, you say? Tell me, Jianyu&mdash;why do you think Eldred&rsquo;s Gothic armor <br />moves so lightly, so swiftly, as though it were silk instead of steel?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="603" data-end="614">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="614" data-end="617" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(blinks, caught off guard)</span></em><br data-start="643" data-end="646" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Because&hellip; because Eldred is a genius?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="686" data-end="701">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="701" data-end="704" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(chuckles, stroking his beard)</span></em><br data-start="734" data-end="737" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">A genius, yes, but also a man who listened&mdash;though he would never admit it. <br />He sharpened his art upon the words of others, mine also. His armor dances because <br />it carries not only his pride, but the whispers of countless guild debates and endless critiques, mine included.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1038" data-end="1049">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1049" data-end="1052" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">So even the greatest smiths&hellip; carry the voices of others inside their work?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1130" data-end="1145">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1145" data-end="1148" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Of course. Do not mistake silence for solitude. Our guilds, our fellow masters, <br />even stern excentric critics like Eldred&mdash;all of them strike their hammers through others in one way or other.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1377" data-end="1388">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1388" data-end="1391" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">To admit such things openly, Master&hellip; does it not make you seem less?</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1474" data-end="1489">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1489" data-end="1492" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(leans closer, his tone warm, yet firm)</span></em><br data-start="1531" data-end="1534" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">No, boy. It makes me more. Strength without humility is brittle, like steel not tempered. <br />Only by bowing to fire and water does iron gain its true resilience. So too with men.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1713" data-end="1724">Jianyu:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1724" data-end="1727" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">I think I understand now. To forge is not to stand alone&hellip; <br />but to stand among many, each lending their hand unseen.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;"><strong data-start="1845" data-end="1860">Liang Shen:</strong></span></em><br data-start="1860" data-end="1863" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">(nods approvingly)</span></em><br data-start="1881" data-end="1884" /><em><span style="color: #8e44ad;">Well said. Remember this, Jianyu: a proud smith may craft armor, <br />but a humble smith crafts legacy.</span></em></h6>			<div style="clear:both;"></div>
		</div>

